From 12d7331be78befd8bbc30c911e5af4830dd266c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 18:09:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(special-situations): replace dead feeds + loosen
 SPIN/TURN/CAP patterns + add SEC EDGAR (0100)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User feedback: 'SPIN: 0 — bad, fix test and again fix until you see something'.

LIVE DIAGNOSTIC (before this patch):
  Total: 13 matches · 10/14 sources OK
  Failed: BS Companies, BS Markets, Reuters Business, Reuters Tech (RSS endpoints dead)
  SPIN: 0 · MA: 10 · TURN: 1 · CAP: 2

FIXES:
1. Replaced dead feeds with working alternatives:
   - BS Companies + BS Markets → MoneyControl Top + MoneyControl Markets +
     MoneyControl Business (ET Markets / Mint Companies stay; ET Stocks added
     as 4th India business feed)
   - Reuters Business + Reuters Tech → CNBC Earnings (Yahoo Finance retained)

2. Added primary corporate-action sources:
   - SEC EDGAR 8-K Atom (real-time M&A / share-issuance / buyback disclosures)
   - SEC EDGAR Form 10-12B Atom (US spin-off prospectuses)
   These are the AUTHORITATIVE sources for US corporate actions; RSS news
   sources reference them but the filings themselves carry the hard signals.

3. Loosened SPIN regex to catch real headline phrasings:
   - 'to separate into two' / 'approves demerger' / 'split into X' /
   - 'creates independent company' / 'NCLT approves scheme of arrangement' /
   - 'business reorganisation' / 'listing of demerged' / Form 10-12B

4. Loosened TURN regex:
   - 'narrowed losses' / 'first profitable quarter' / 'EBITDA positive' /
   - 'operating profit after' / 'recovers from loss' / 'CDR exit' /
   - 'insolvency exit' / 'emerges from restructuring'

5. Expanded MA to catch:
   - 'stake sale' / 'sells business/unit/division' / 'CCI approves' /
   - 'definitive agreement' / 'definitive merger'

6. Expanded CAP to include India equity-raise events:
   - 'QIP' / 'qualified institutional placement' / 'rights issue' /
   - 'preferential allotment' / 'board approves dividend'

Source list now: 18 RSS feeds (was 14). Pattern matching ~3x looser on SPIN
and TURN; reject patterns kept tight to kill rumour / negation noise.

Type-check clean.
